Bug: We use git-flow which creates branches like "feature/my-branch-name".  When I went to create a pull request from this branch I got a popup that stated: "An error occurred.  Something went wrong while trying to serve your request.  Try reloading the page."  I created a new branch which ONLY replaced the '/' with a '-' character and it worked fine.  When re-trying the version with '/' I hit the Escape key instead of the "Reload the page" button and found that the Pull Request was actually created with the '/' in spite of the error.

I can't wait to see the version with branch/repo permissions, Pull Requests invites and +1 approval of pull requests to trigger the final merge.
