We should add syntax highlighting for hpp extensions to Stash. 

The syntax highlighting is applied based on the rules set at the following javascript file:
{code}
./webapps/ROOT/static/feature/file-content/source-view/source-view.js
{code}

To mave "hpp" recognized as C++, you can open the file and locate the following line:
{code}
cpp : { exts : ['cpp', 'h', 'c', 'cc', 'cxx'], exes : []},
{code}
Then add the new hpp extension to the list:
{code}
cpp : { exts : ['cpp', 'h', 'c', 'cc', 'cxx', 'hpp'], exes : []},
{code}
And save the file.

This file is bundled to the batch.js which is cached by our js injection plugin. So to make sure the new version of the js file will be used, please remove all the content of the following folder and then restart Stash:
{code}
STASH-HOME/caches/webresources
{code}

with a home dir set as a relative path: 'home':

After creating a new repository and following the instructions in the UI for pushing to it, the client reports:

{noformat}
test (master) $ git push origin master
Password for 'http://someuser@localhost:7990': 
error: The requested URL returned error: 501 while accessing http://someuser@localhost:7990/scm/STASH/stash.git/info/refs
fatal: HTTP request failed
{noformat}
The server log contains:

{noformat}
2012-08-02 11:55:39,425 WARN  [http-7990-3] someuser 715x159x1 yduhpd 172.20.6.162 /git/STASH/stash.git/info/refs c.a.stash.internal.scm.ScmServlet Invalid request from host 172.20.6.162: Note that Stash does not support gits legacy HTTP transport protocol.
{noformat}

After much head-scratching, we turned on debug logging and found:

{noformat}
2012-08-02 12:23:46,283 DEBUG [http-7990-1] someuser 743x3x1 1uj69fn 127.0.0.1 /scm/STASH/stash.git/info/refs c.a.s.i.scm.git.web.GitSmartRequest write process succeeded, but it logged this to the error console
: Not a git repository: 'home/data/repositories/1'
{noformat}

Need to either reject the home path, resolve it to an absolute one before passing it git, or give better error messages so a user can diagnose it themselves.

e.g. {code}
An error occurred while executing an external process: Expected diff header, but found [[1mdiff --git src://file.txt dst://file.txt[m]
{code}

See https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/66124/error-viewing-diffs-during-stash-development-on-osx

Stash should use the --no-color option when running diff, or otherwise ignore global config settings.

Since upgrade to version 1.1 the Git HTTP access is broken. The error message is:
{quote}
fatal: remote error: Repository does not exists
The requested repository does not exists, or you do not have permissions to access it.
{quote}

I have tried to clone the repository with the old URL format:
{quote}http://user@stash.domain.com/git/PROJECTKEY/repo.git{quote}
or the new URL format:
{quote}http://user@stash.domain.com/scm/PROJECTKEY/repo.git{quote}

But none of them works.

The workaround is to use the newly provided SSH access.
